<subsection xml:id="subsec-plotting-points-on-the-cartesian-plane-in-different-situations">
    <title>Plotting Points on the Cartesian Plane in Different Situations</title>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Consider the points B (-7,2), Y (8,-4), L (3,3), K (0,-5), A (5,-2) and Z (-6,-5)
            <ol marker="(a).">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Draw a Cartesian plane and plot the given points.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Discuss as a group and compare your graphs with the rest in class.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A school wants to create a mini park on its playground. The park will have four trees planted at specific locations, forming a rectangular area. The positions of the trees are given as:
            </p>
            <p>
                A <m>(2,3)</m>,B <m>(2,7)</m>,C <m>(6,7)</m>,D <m>(6,3)</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Plot these points on a Cartesian plane.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Identify the shape formed by connecting the points.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the length and width of the rectangle.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                    
                        <image>
                            <latex-image label="k">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    % Draw grid
                                    \draw[very thin,gray!50] (0,0) grid (8,8);
                                    
                                    % Draw x and y axes
                                    \draw[thick,->] (-1,0) -- (8.5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                                    \draw[thick,->] (0,-1) -- (0,8.5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
                                    
                                    % Tick marks and labels
                                    \foreach \x in {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8} {
                                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1);
                                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                                    }

                                    \foreach \y in {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8} {
                                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y);
                                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                                    }

                                    % Origin
                                    \node[anchor=north east] at (-0.1,-0.1) {\textbf{0}};

                                    % Plot points and labels
                                    \fill[red] (2,3) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north east] {\textbf{A}};
                                    \fill[blue] (2,7) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south east] {\textbf{B}};
                                    \fill[green] (6,7) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south west] {\textbf{C}};
                                    \fill[orange] (6,3) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north west] {\textbf{D}};

                                    % Connect the points to form a rectangle
                                    \draw[thick] (2,3) -- (2,7) -- (6,7) -- (6,3) -- cycle;
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                            
                        </image>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Connecting the points in order forms a rectangle.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Finding Length and Width:
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                         Distance between A and B or C and D (same x-coordinates) = <m>\textbf{7 - 3 = 4}\textbf{units (height)}</m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                         Distance between A and D or B and C (same y-coordinates) = <m>\textbf{6 - 2 = 4}\textbf{units (width)}</m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            The dimensions of the rectangle are 4 Ã— 4 units (a square).
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>  
            </p>          
        </solution>
    </example>
</subsection>